This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: Image Slider
item.dc:creator: btoa
item.content:encoded:
[header style="" type="h3" id="image-hovers"]Image Slider[/header]

With just a few lines of shortcodes (don't worry, it's all done with the help of the visual editor!), you can have the slider below working in no time. It features a thumbnail slider (optional), lightbox integration and a description!

[divider_top text=""] [header style="" type="h3" id="image-hovers"]Basic Usage:[/header] [padding size="5"]

The slider is basically composed of two parts. A wrapping shortcode called "image_slider" where you define your width, height, selector and autoslide time, and multiple children "slide_item" shortcodes, in which you define your slides individually. These are the attributes each shortcode gets:

[column size="one-half"]

"image_slider"

  • width: Width of your slide. Images bigger than this will be cut out (you can use timthumb as well)
    Default: 900
  • height: Height of your slide. Images bigger than this will be cut out (you can use timthumb as well)
    Default: 300
  • selector: Whether or not to show the thumbnails selector.
    Options: true, false — Default: true
  • autoslide: Time in miliseconds for how long to wait in each slide. Don't use to disable it.
    Default: none
[/column] [column size="one-half" last="last"]

"slide_item"

  • title: Title of your slide. Displays at the bottom left.
  • description: Description of your slide. Displays smaller than text at the bottom left.
  • type: Whether to display as lightbox or link upon click.
    Options: lightbox, link — Default: lightbox

Image hovers are a simple way to add a nice hover effect to your images. By wrapping them around the shortcode "image_hover" The following effects can be created. Image hovers accept links and other shortcodes attached to the image. See further examples for more info.

[padding size="10"]

These are the attributes image_hover can take:

[column size="one-half"]

  • icon: Insert here the full URL for a custom icon. This icon will be centered aligned.
  • align: Whether to align the image left or right. Useful when using within blocs of text.
    Options: left, right — Default: none
[/column] [column size="one-half" last="true"]

[header style="" type="h3"]Some info before you go on[/header]

The column template is based on percentages. Meaning that no matter where you put a one-half column, it will always be half of that total width.

Take some time to read these 4 blocks of information.

[padding size="15"] [column size="one-fourth"] [header style="" type="h3"]Size[/header]

The column shortcode has only one base shortcode, but many attributes. You will always use the shortcode "column", but changing the attribute size="".

[/column] [column size="one-fourth"] [header style="" type="h3"]Last Columns[/header]

Whenever you're setting a group of columns, the last one that closes the whole block, will need the last attribute. For example, when we have 3 columns with size one-third, the third column will have the attribute last="true"

[/column] [column size="one-fourth"] [header style="" type="h3"]Columns Inside Columns[/header]

You are most welcome to put columns inside columns. A one-half column inside a one-half column will consequently give you a one-fourth column. Just keep in mind that this may cause troubles, so add a _ sign in front of the shortcode

[/column] [column size="one-fourth" last="last"] [padding size="49"]

For example. If you have a one-half inside a one-half, The child column, instead of being [raw][column size="one-half][/raw] it will be [raw][_column size="one-half][/raw]. You can add up to 5 _ signs.

item.title: Company Secretary
item.dc:creator: btoa
item.content:encoded:
• ASX Listed
  • High performance culture
  • People management
My client is a leading ASX Listed financial services business with a wide product offering and a proud history of strong returns for their shareholders and investors. The business has a strong commitment to investing in their staff and developing their capabilities. Due to an internal promotion an experienced Company Secretary is required to join the Legal and Secretariat function. The Company Secretary will report directly to the Group General Counsel and Company Secretary who has a strong reputation in the business and strong management experience in management of both in-house Legal Counsel and Company Secretaries. The Company Secretary will be responsible for the management of a small team of professional and administrative staff and ensuring worlds best practice and a high level of service delivery is extended to internal and external stakeholders.
